javax.accessibility.Accessible, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable
public class AttributeTypesPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel

Displays the types of attributes on the table and stores them in a DataSet. When a user confirms the types of attributes, the DataSet will make statistics for the continuous attributes and estimate the distribution of the labels for categorical attributes.
Initially only 'Categorical' and 'Continuous' type will be displayed and 'Ordinal' type column is not activated. When a user choose 'K-Means' model, the ordinal types column will be activated, and the program requires a user to confirm the attribute types again.

AttributeTableModel is an inner class which extends AbstractTableModel. Modified from WEKA-3-2-3.
